==Korean==
===Noun===
'''해''' (hae) 
# [[sun]], [[sunlight]]
# [[daytime]]
# [[year]], (prefix)  [[yearly]]
# ([[海]]) [[sea]]
# ([[害]]) [[damage]], [[evil]], [[harm]], [[injury]] 

====Antonyms====
* [[달]] (dal) [[moon]]

====Derived terms====
* 해바라기 (-baragi) [[sunflower]]
* 햅[[쌀]] (haeb-ssal, haep-) [[rice]] of the year
* 햇[[것]] (haes-geos) [[produce]] of the year
* 햇[[귀]] (haes-gwi) [[sunbeam]] (literally, "sun's ear") 
* 햇귀엣[[골]] (haes-gwi-es-gol) [[solar]] [[halo]] (literally, "sun's-ear-at-ring", hence "ring around the sun's ear" looking like a wheel!  cf. Old English [[hweol|hweoġol]] "wheel" almost sounding like "ring of the sun" in obsolete Korean, i.e., 해의골 (hae-ui-gol) in modern Korean.)  
* 햇[[무리]] (haes-muri) [[solar]] [[halo]]
* 햇[[볕]] (haes-byeot) [[sunshine]] (mainly in terms of heat) 
* 햇[[빛]] (haes-bich, -bit) [[sunlight]]
* 햇[[살]] (haes-sal) [[sunbeam]] (literally, "solar arrow," suggesting penetration)

====Related terms====
* 날 (nal) [[day]]
* 낮 (naj, nat) [[daytime]]
* 하루 (haru) [[one]] [[day]], [[daytime]]

